{
  "stem": "15577.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That means eating by the work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then you came at home not hungry.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The second possibility was, which was use especially by people who wanted to earn money, is to smuggle food for the others.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "If they succeeded, it was very good.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "If they didn't succeed, so there were many, many, many cases when not only people were caught smuggling food were punished, but every set, every 10, all the group and so, there were all even cases when they shot the people who were smuggling food.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This was the way how the-- but as long as ghetto existed-- I am speaking about the Crakow ghetto-- there was still-- many people were in touch with Polish people, all the working places.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Oh, they were coming through the fences, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They-- they knew somebody was selling and buying.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It wasn't-- it was very dangerous, but-- but it was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after the war when I-- even during the war-- when I knew what was going on, let's say in Warsaw ghetto, where the majority was hunger and very, very poor, so Crakow ghetto, there was hunger, and there were poor people, but I think that on the-- on general-- in general, we managed.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Where did you work?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was working when-- today I would call it garage.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a very special garage, which belonged to a Jew [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] before the war, then it was taken by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the Jew still managed it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a very-- he was a very well-known mechanic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a very special garage which was for cars.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, at that time, the electrical-- how do you call-- generator?",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
